lyrics.stanza:
Through Thy precious body broken&mdash;
    Inside the veil;
Oh! what words to sinners spoken&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
Precious as the blood that bought us;
Perfect, as the love that sought us;
Holy, as the Lamb that brought us&mdash;
    Inside the veil.

When we see Thy love unshaken&mdash;
    Outside the camp.
Scorned by man, by God forsaken&mdash;
    Outside the camp.
Thy loved cross alone can charm us;
Shame need now no more alarm us;
Glad we follow, nought can harm us&mdash;
    Outside the camp.

Lamb of God, through Thee we enter&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
Cleansed by Thee, we boldly venture&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
Not a stain; a new creation:
Ours is such a full salvation;
Low we bow in adoration&mdash;
    Inside the veil.

Unto Thee, the homeless stranger&mdash;
    Outside the camp,
Forth we hasten, fear no danger&mdash;
    Outside the camp.
Thy reproach, far richer treasure
Than all Egypt's boasted pleasure;
Drawn by love that knows no measure&mdash;
    Outside the camp.

Soon Thy saints shall all be gathered&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
All with Thee&mdash;no more be scattered&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
Nought from Thee, our hearts shall sever;
We shall see Thee; grieve Thee never;
"Praise the Lamb!" shall sound forever&mdash;
    Inside the veil.
